# Delivery Pipeline Framework

## Pipeline Paths

| Path | Risk | Stages |
|---|---|---|
| S | 1–2 | `ba → tech-lead → dev → reviewer (inline QA)` |
| M | 3 | `ba → sa → [designer?] → tech-lead → dev → qa → reviewer` |
| L | 4–5 | `ba → sa → [security-design?] → tech-lead → dev → [devops?] → qa → [security-review?] → reviewer` |

`ba` handles both BA + domain modeling (no separate `domain-analyst` stage).
`[]` = conditional stage. Stage gates, verdicts → AGENTS.md.

---

## Feature Location Convention

| Repo type | Features root | feature-map.yaml |
|---|---|---|
| mini | `docs/features/` | Recommended |
| mono — app | `{project-path}/docs/features/` | **Required** |
| mono — service | `{project-path}/docs/features/` | **Required** |
| mono — cross-cutting | `docs/features/` | **Required** |
| hotfix (any) | `docs/hotfixes/` | Recommended |

**`docs/feature-map.yaml`** at workspace root is the PRIMARY lookup index.
All state writers (new-feature, from-doc, hotfix) create/update this file.
All state readers (resume-feature, feature-status, close-feature, update-feature) read it FIRST.

