| `/ui-catalog` | `docs/ui-library/{template}-catalog.md` | `designer`, `fe-dev` |

---

## Context Compression

After every 3 completed stages: snapshot to `_state.md`.
On `/resume-feature`: read snapshot — not full artifact history.
Pass `docs-path` to agents (not full artifact content inline).

---

## Doc Generation Pipeline

Separate pipeline for generating documentation from source code or description files.
Uses `doc-*` agents, same Dispatcher, same `_state.md` schema with `pipeline-type: doc-generation`.

| Stage | Agent | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `doc-intel` | `doc-intel` | Input is description files → extract semantic content. Via `/from-doc` |
| `research` | `doc-researcher` | Scan codebase: stack, routes/APIs/DB, flows, FE. 4 phases |
| `test-runner` | `doc-test-runner` | Playwright scripts → screenshots. Requires Docker |
| `doc-gen-phase` | 5 parallel writers | Generate doc files from intel reports |
| `doc-export` | `doc-exporter` | Fill Office templates (.xlsx, .docx) |

Entry skills: `/from-doc` (Claude Code or Cursor), `/generate-docs`, `/export-docs`

SDLC vs Doc pipeline:
- SDLC: build code from requirements → `ba/`, `sa/`, `05-dev-*.md`
- Doc: document existing code → `intel/*.json`, `output/*.md`
- Both share Dispatcher and `_state.md` schema; distinguished by `pipeline-type` field
